Cover a baking sheet with aluminum foil. Cook and stir butter, cashews, 3/4 cup sugar, dried mint, cayenne pepper, cumin, and coriander in a skillet over medium-low heat until sugar has dissolved and cashews are browned, 7 to 10 minutes. Spread cashews over the prepared baking sheet to cool. Place lemon juice and 1/2 cup sugar in a blender. Blend until sugar is dissolved. Add coconut milk and ginger; blend until smooth. Combine watermelon, cantaloupe, kiwi, apple, raisins, and shredded coconut in a large bowl Pour coconut mixture over fruit and gently toss to coat. Sprinkle cooled cashews over fruit salad.